OL,3,CPlans to change school holidays in
OL,4,CWales are shelved
OL,6,FMore than half of those who responded
OL,7,Fto the consultation wanted the school
OL,8,Fcalendar re-structured. Of those who
OL,9,Fresponded, parents, governors, and
OL,10,Fyouth workers were broadly in favour
OL,11,Fof changes while teachers, unions and
OL,12,Ftourism organisations were broadly
OL,13,Fagainst.
OL,15,FAny decision to go ahead with the
OL,16,Fchanges to school holidays in future
OL,17,Fwould be taken after the next Welsh
OL,18,FParliament election in May 2026,
OL,19,Fmaking any change to the school
OL,20,Fholidays unlikely before the 2028-2029
OL,21,Fschool year.
